### 7. Verify Payment Signature (Order or Subscription)
# Verifies payment signature for both one-time orders and subscriptions
# Uses HMAC SHA256 signature verification with key_secret from environment variables
# 
# Body Parameters:
# - razorpay_order_id: Razorpay order ID (required for order payments, string)
# - razorpay_subscription_id: Razorpay subscription ID (required for subscription payments, string)
# - razorpay_payment_id: Razorpay payment ID (required, string)
# - razorpay_signature: Payment signature from Razorpay (required, string)
#   Generated by Razorpay and returned after payment completion
# 
# Signature Generation (as per Razorpay docs):
# - For ORDERS: hmac_sha256(order_id + "|" + payment_id, secret)
# - For SUBSCRIPTIONS: hmac_sha256(payment_id + "|" + subscription_id, secret)
# Note: The order of IDs is DIFFERENT for subscriptions vs orders!
# 
# Security:
# - The key_secret is ONLY read from environment variables (RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET)
# - Never send your key_secret in the request body
# - Signature verification ensures payment authenticity
# 
# Notes:
# - Provide EITHER razorpay_order_id OR razorpay_subscription_id (not both)
# - The signature is generated by Razorpay and returned to your client
# - Server verifies the signature using the secret from environment variables
# 
# Response (200 OK - Order Payment):
# {
#   "verified": true,
#   "message": "Order payment verified successfully",
#   "entityType": "order"
# }
# 
# Response (200 OK - Subscription Payment):
# {
#   "verified": true,
#   "message": "Subscription payment verified successfully",
#   "entityType": "subscription"
# }
# 
# Response (400 Bad Request):
# {
#   "verified": false,
#   "error": "Invalid signature"
# }
# OR
# {
#   "error": "Missing required parameters. Provide either razorpay_order_id or razorpay_subscription_id along with razorpay_payment_id and razorpay_signature"
# }
# 
# Response (500 Internal Server Error):
# {
#   "error": "Verification failed"
# }
# 
# Database Updates:
# - For orders: Updates order status to "captured" and stores razorpayPaymentId
# - For subscriptions: Updates subscription status to "active"

### 7a. Verify Order Payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/razorpay/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "razorpay_order_id": "order_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "razorpay_payment_id": "pay_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "razorpay_signature": "signature_XXXXXXXXXXXXX"
}

### 7b. Verify Subscription Payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/razorpay/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "razorpay_subscription_id": "sub_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "razorpay_payment_id": "pay_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "razorpay_signature": "signature_XXXXXXXXXXXXX"
}

### ===== RAZORPAY SUBSCRIPTIONS =====

### Create Subscription
# Creates a new subscription with Razorpay
# 
# Authentication: Required (via session cookies or Bearer token)
# The user ID is automatically extracted from the authenticated session
# 
# Body Parameters:
# - plan_id: Razorpay plan ID (required, string)
# - quantity: Number of subscriptions (optional, default: 1)
# - total_count: Total billing cycles (optional, default: 100)
# - start_at: Subscription start timestamp in UNIX seconds (optional, defaults to 24 hours from now)
# - notes: Additional metadata (required, must include email, contact)
#   - email: User's email (required, string)
#   - contact: User's phone number (required, string, e.g., "+919876543210")
# 
# Features:
# - First payment addon of ₹5 (500 paise) charged immediately
# - Full subscription charge happens after 24 hours when subscription activates
# - Automatic customer creation/lookup
# - Database persistence with subscription tracking
# 
# Response (200 OK):
# {
#   "subscription": {
#     "id": "sub_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "plan_id": "plan_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "customer_id": "cust_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "status": "created",
#     "quantity": 1,
#     "start_at": 1234567890,
#     "charge_at": 1234567890,
#     ...
#   },
#   "razorpaySubscription": {
#     "key": "rzp_test_XXXXXXXX",
#     "subscription_id": "sub_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "name": "AlertPay Premium",
#     "description": "Monthly subscription",
#     "image": undefined,
#     "callback_url": undefined,
#     "amount": 15000,
#     "currency": "INR",
#     "prefill": {
#       "name": undefined,
#       "email": "test@example.com",
#       "contact": "+919876543210"
#     },
#     "notes": { ... },
#     "theme": {
#       "color": "#F37254"
#     }
#   },
#   "subscriptionId": "abc12345",
#   "customerId": "cust_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#   "message": "Subscription created successfully. First payment of ₹5 will be charged immediately."
# }
# 
# Response (400 Bad Request):
# {
#   "error": "plan_id is required" | "email and contact are required in notes"
# }
# 
# Response (401 Unauthorized):
# {
#   "error": "Unauthorized - no valid session"
# }
# 
# Response (500 Internal Server Error):
# {
#   "error": "Failed to create subscription" | "Failed to create or find customer"
# }
POST {{localUrl}}/razorpay/subscriptions/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plan_id": "plan_S3FaBrk7sjPQEU",
  "quantity": 1,
  "total_count": 12,
  "notes": {
    "email": "rajatdhoot123@gmail.com",
    "contact": "+918855866494"
  }
}

### Create Subscription - With Bearer Token
POST {{baseUrlProd}}/razorpay/subscriptions/v1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "plan_id": "plan_S3FaBrk7sjPQEU",
  "quantity": 1,
  "total_count": 12,
  "notes": {
    "email": "rajatdhoot123@gmail.com",
    "contact": "+918855866494"
  }
}

### Create Subscription v2 - With UPI Flow Support
# Enhanced version of subscription endpoint with UPI flow control (Intent vs Collect)
# 
# Authentication: Required (via session cookies or Bearer token)
# App ID Required: X-App-ID header (e.g., "alertpay-android")
# 
# Body Parameters:
# - plan_id: Razorpay plan ID (required, string)
# - quantity: Number of subscriptions (optional, default: 1)
# - start_at: Subscription start timestamp in UNIX seconds (optional, defaults to 24 hours from now)
# - notes: Additional metadata (required, must include email, contact)
#   - email: User's email (required, string)
#   - contact: User's phone number (required, string, e.g., "+919876543210")
# - flow: UPI payment flow type (optional, default: "intent")
#   - "intent": UPI intent flow (opens UPI apps directly)
#   - "collect": UPI collect flow (sends payment request to UPI ID)
# - vpa: UPI ID/VPA (required for collect flow, string, e.g., "user@ybl")
# 
# UPI Flow Types:
# - Intent Flow: Opens UPI apps (Google Pay, PhonePe, etc.) directly on user's device
#   Best for mobile apps where user has UPI apps installed
# - Collect Flow: Sends payment request to user's UPI ID
#   Best for web or when you know user's VPA
# 
# Features:
# - First payment addon of ₹5 (500 paise) charged immediately
# - Full subscription charge happens after 24 hours when subscription activates
# - Automatic customer creation/lookup
# - Database persistence with subscription tracking
# - Multi-app isolation (same user can have different subscriptions per app)
# 
# Response (200 OK):
# {
#   "subscription": {
#     "id": "sub_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "plan_id": "plan_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "customer_id": "cust_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "status": "created",
#     "quantity": 1,
#     "start_at": 1234567890,
#     "charge_at": 1234567890,
#     ...
#   },
#   "razorpaySubscription": {
#     "key": "rzp_test_XXXXXXXX",
#     "subscription_id": "sub_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#     "name": "AlertPay Premium",
#     "description": "Monthly subscription",
#     "amount": 500,
#     "max_amount": 15000,
#     "currency": "INR",
#     "prefill": {
#       "name": undefined,
#       "email": "test@example.com",
#       "contact": "+919876543210"
#     },
#     "notes": { ... },
#     "theme": {
#       "color": "#F37254"
#     },
#     "_[flow]": "intent",
#     "vpa": "user@ybl" // Only present for collect flow
#   },
#   "subscriptionId": "abc12345",
#   "customerId": "cust_XXXXXXXXXXXXX",
#   "message": "Subscription created successfully. First payment of ₹5 will be charged immediately."
# }
# 
# Response (400 Bad Request):
# {
#   "error": "plan_id is required" | "email and contact are required in notes" | 
#            "flow must be either 'intent' or 'collect'" | 
#            "vpa (UPI ID) is required for collect flow"
# }
# 
# Response (401 Unauthorized):
# {
#   "error": "Unauthorized - no valid session" | "Invalid or disabled app identifier"
# }
# 
# Response (500 Internal Server Error):
# {
#   "error": "Failed to create subscription" | "Failed to create or find customer"
# }
POST {{localUrl}}/razorpay/subscriptions/v2
Content-Type: application/json
X-App-ID: alertpay-android

{
  "plan_id": "plan_S3FaBrk7sjPQEU",
  "quantity": 1,
  "flow": "intent",
  "notes": {
    "email": "rajatdhoot123@gmail.com",
    "contact": "+918855866494"
  }
}

### Create Subscription v2 - Production (Intent Flow)
POST {{localUrl}}/razorpay/subscriptions/v2
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
X-App-ID: alertpay-android

{
